=E2=80=94<strong>R.F.K. Jr.</strong> to lead H.H.S.; <strong>Tulsi Gabbard<=
/strong> as D.N.I.; and <strong>Kash Patel</strong> to run the F.B.I.=E2=80=
=94are finally facing their respective moments of truth. As of now, Gabbard=
 appears most embattled. Last week, the former Hawaii congresswoman and Dem=
ocratic presidential candidate, and current lieutenant colonel in the Army =
Reserves, turned in an uneven performance in
pursuit of the nation=E2=80=99s top intelligence post.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:=
0px;">Some senators thought she did well in her private, one-on-one meeting=
s in the weeks leading up to the hearing. For instance, she apparently assu=
aged Senator <strong>Susan Collins</strong>=E2=80=99s concerns about some o=
f her troubling overseas meetings, including with Syria=E2=80=99s now-depos=
ed despot <strong>Bashar al-Assad</strong>, and another with Shia religious
figures in Lebanon that might have included Hezbollah officials (a suggesti=
on she called =E2=80=9Cabsurd=E2=80=9D in her hearing). Alas, I=E2=80=99m t=
old other private meetings didn=E2=80=99t go as well. Gabbard had to spend =
too much time explaining herself.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Her public hearing, meanwhile, se=
emed to begin fortuitously: Republicans on the Hill were shocked when forme=
r North Carolina senator <strong>Richard Burr</strong> agreed to introduce
Gabbard. The respected former chair of the Intelligence Committee is no Tru=
mp acolyte=E2=80=94he led the committee=E2=80=99s investigation into allega=
tions of Russian interference in the 2016 election, despite political press=
ure from Trump to dismiss it. Burr, now a non-lobbyist =E2=80=9Cpolicy advi=
sor=E2=80=9D at the lobbying firm DLA Piper, brought a <em>gravitas</em> th=
at somewhat legitimized Gabbard=E2=80=99s nomination for some Republicans, =
including Senator <strong>Lindsey Graham</strong>, who announced today that=
 he would vote
for her. And though he politely declined an interview request, I was told B=
urr had worked closely with Gabbard before, and he testified that he was fr=
ustrated by what he called a =E2=80=9Csmear campaign=E2=80=9D against her.=
